Authors: Agtriadi H.B., Chandra N., Warnars H.L.H.S., Gaol F.L.
Title: Software size measurement with use case point for employee application software at STT-PLN
Source title: 2017 IEEE International Conference on Cybernetics and Computational Intelligence, CyberneticsCOM 2017 - Proceedings
Affiliations: Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program - Doctor of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; STT-PLN, Jakarta, Indonesia; Mobile Application and Technology Program, Computer Science Department, School of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Agtriadi, H.B., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program - Doctor of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia, STT-PLN, Jakarta, Indonesia; Chandra, N., Mobile Application and Technology Program, Computer Science Department, School of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Warnars, H.L.H.S., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program - Doctor of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Gaol, F.L., STT-PLN, Jakarta, Indonesia
Abstract: Employee Application (EA) is a system information for realizing the latest personal data and integrated, provide accurate employee information for planning, development, welfare and control of employees. EA in STT-PLN began to be published since 2013. The software size of the EA STT-PLN will be measured with use case point method. Measurement of the software size of EA STT-PLN will be measured with Use Case Point upon use case diagram for EA STT-PLN as shown in the project has small software size where score Use Case Point (UCP) = 70.34. UCP is another alternative implementation method which can be applied to measure application software size whenever needed to deal with time, money and people. © 2017 IEEE.

Index Keywords: Artificial intelligence; Personnel; Software Measurement; Software metrics; Software project; Software size; System information; Use case diagram; Use case points; Application programs
